1 "D. Procurements pursuant to this Section may include single award or
2 multiple award ID/IQ construction contracts. The legislature authorizes the
3 department and the office of Louisiana highway construction to procure ID/IQ
4 contracts using low bid and best value methods, and to award such contracts and any
5 resulting work orders using low bid or best value, as specified in the solicitation
6 documents. All procurement documents issued by the department and the office of
7 Louisiana highway construction, respectively, including the NOI and RFP, shall
8 indicate whether a single award or multiple awards will be made. Materials
9 separately acquired by the department or office of Louisiana highway construction
10 may be provided to contractors for use under and as a condition of any ID/IQ
11 contract.
12 E. Procurement and award of ID/IQ construction contacts shall meet the
13 following requirements
14 (1) Single award ID/IQ construction contracts procured on a low-bid basis
15 may be advertised and awarded using one of the following methods:
16 (a) In accordance with R.S. 48:252 and 255 for award to the lowest
17 responsive and responsible bidder; or
18 (b) In accordance with the advertisement and award procedures set forth in
19 this Section.
20 (2) Multiple-award ID/IQ construction contracts may be procured on a low
21 bid or best value basis, as determined by the department and office of Louisiana
22 highway construction, respectively. Such procurements shall be conducted in
23 accordance with applicable Louisiana public bid and procurement laws including the
24 requirements for advertisements and the procedures set forth in this Section.
25 (3)(a)The procurement of any multiple-award ID/IQ construction contract or
26 a single award ID/IQ construction contract not advertised and awarded pursuant to
27 R.S. 48:252 and 255, shall commence with the department and the office of
28 Louisiana highway construction, respectively, issuing a "notice of intent" (NOI)
29 through advertisement on their designated webpages to request letters of interest
30 (LOI). The NOI shall be advertised for at least ten business days prior to the deadline
31 for submission of LOI and shall include a description of the ID/IQ services to be
32 procured. The department and the office of Louisiana highway construction may also
33 readvertise the NOI using additional media or publications and may readvertise as
34 necessary if the number of responses received is deemed insufficient to ensure
35 adequate competition."
36 (b) After the deadline for submission of LOI for a single-award or
37 multiple-award ID/IQ construction contract, the department and office of Louisiana
38 highway construction shall issue a Request for Proposals ("RFP") to all contractors
39 that submitted an LOI. The RFP shall include instructions for proposal preparation
40 and submission, a description of the evaluation methodology, and shall comply with
41 the requirements of this Section.
42 (c) Bid bonds in accordance with R.S. 48:253 shall be specified in the
43 department and the office of Louisiana highway construction's standard
44 specifications or special provisions. The department and the office of Louisiana
45 highway construction may waive the requirement for bid bonds for procurements
46 under this Section.
47 (4)(a) The assistant secretary for project delivery, with the concurrence of the
48 secretary or designee, and the executive director of the office of Louisiana highway
49 construction , respectively, shall establish an evaluation committee for evaluation of
50 proposals received in response to the RFP. The evaluation committee may, in its
51 discretion, be assisted by other departments and office of Louisiana highway
52 construction personnel and external advisors in the evaluation the proposals.
53 (b) The evaluation committee shall evaluate the proposals and make a
54 recommendation of award to the secretary and executive director. The secretary,
55 executive director, or their designees, shall make the final determination of award.
56 (5) Prior to issuing a work order under a multiple-award ID/IQ construction
57 contract, the department and the office of Louisiana highway construction,
58 respectively, shall solicit competitive responses from the contractors awarded ID/IQ
59 contracts under the solicitation in accordance with procedures set forth in the ID/IQ
60 construction contract. The procurement documents or contract shall state the
61 procedures and selection criteria for issuance of work orders. Work orders shall be
62 awarded on a competitive low bid basis, or, where permitted by applicable law and
